# 2. 完璧になりたくて

Host: You're so slender, and you have such long arms and legs. I'm so jealous...! You're like a life-size doll!
Shizuku: Hehe. I appreciate your compliments.
Host: Oh wow! You even glow when you laugh! It's like you're beauty incarnate!
Senior Member: Isn't she though? Her aura's so bright that we might need to start carrying parasols around with us!
Shizuku: (Okay, so far, I've managed to keep to the script...)
Shizuku: (This live program will be over in just a little bit, but I need to stay focused until the end.)
MC: Alright, let's finish by asking our new lead here about her aspirations for the future.
Shizuku: Yes, as the lead...
Shizuku: As the lead...
Shizuku: (No... I practiced reading this part so many times! Why am I drawing a blank now...?)
MC: Ms. Hinomori...?
Shizuku: I... Um...
Senior Member: Try to relax, Shizuku... You're tensing up so much that it's showing on your face.
Senior Member: But I guess it means you're just that excited. I'm sure Cheerful * Days has a bright future ahead of it as long as you maintain that sort of energy.
Shizuku: (*Gasp* Thank you...!)
Shizuku: Yes...
Shizuku: As the lead, I'd like to do everything in my power to take Cheerful * Days to greater heights.
Shizuku: So, we'll be looking forward to your continued support.
MC: Yes, I think we're all looking forward to seeing where Cheerful * Days goes! And thank you for joining us today!
Manager: Nice work, everyone! That went really well.
Manager: Although, Shizuku, that last part was concerning. Your fans want to see the perfect you, so please try to keep that in mind for next time.
Shizuku: Y-Yes, I will...!
Shizuku: *Sigh*
Shizuku: (All I had to do was say what was written in the script. Why am I having so much trouble with that...?)
Shizuku: (I need to do a better job of being the “perfect Shizuku Hinomori”...)
???: <Here comes Happy Everyday as requested!>
Shizuku: Oh, that voice...
Airi on TV: <Hey, what's this giant hole doing here?! Whose idea was it to make me fall into it right after I appeared?!>
Shizuku: Airi...
Shizuku: (She's so incredible. Recently, I've been seeing her on TV at least once a week...)
Shizuku: I don't have time to feel sad. I need to try harder, like Airi...!
Senior Member: Nice work out there, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Oh, hello...! Thank you for what you did just now!
Senior Member: Haha. Anytime. Things are more fun when we help each other out.
Senior Member: Also, I kinda want you to do well since I'll be stepping away from the group soon, you know...?
Shizuku: I-I'll do my best!
Senior Member: Hehe. We know that you're a hard-working girl, Shizuku, but try not to work too hard. It's important to relax sometimes.
Shizuku: R-Right...!
Senior Member: That reminds me. You're entering high school soon, right? Miya Girls, was it?
Shizuku: Yes. The manager suggested that I go there since I mentioned that I wanted to put some effort into my studies.
Senior Member: That's great! And everyone keeps saying how nice Miya Girls is!
Senior Member: Being an idol and a student at the same time isn't easy, but I'm sure everything you learn will be to your benefit. So, good luck.
Shizuku: Yes, thank you!
Senior Member: Also, have you thought about joining a club...? I mean, you only get one chance to enjoy your youth!
Shizuku: A club...? Actually, would you mind if I asked which club you were in?
Senior Member: I was in the archery club! Three years of that did wonders for my posture.
Shizuku: Archery...
Senior Member: Yup. But there are plenty of other fun clubs to choose from, so you should choose the one that suits you best, Shizuku.
Shizuku: I see... I think I'll try a few different ones first.
Shizuku: *Sigh* Thank goodness I was able to find the gate.
Shizuku: Now, where is my class...? They said that it should be posted on the bulletin board...
New Students: Huh?! Isn't that Shizuku Hinomori?!
New Students: She goes here?! Whoa! She's so pretty...!
Shizuku: Oh...
Shizuku: (Right. Many of my fans are going to be here. I can't let my guard down...)
???: Shizuku!!!
Shizuku: Huh? Oh...!
Shizuku: Airi! I'd heard that we'd be going to school together, but I didn't expect to see you so soon...!
Airi: Not just that! We're in the same class! Talk about a happy coincidence!
Shizuku: Yes, it really is!
Airi: To be fair, the credit-based course doesn't have that many people in it, so I guess the odds of being put together were higher than normal.
Airi: Anyway, Shizuku, I'm looking forward to having a great year together!
Shizuku: *Gasp* We're really in the same class! I couldn't be happier...!
Airi: Oh, you. I get that you're happy, but you're acting like a Golden Retriever with its tail wagging around...
Airi: Oh, there's the bell...! Let's go!
Shizuku: Okay!
Teacher: You'll all be going home for the day now...
Teacher: But starting tomorrow, you will all have an opportunity to see what our clubs have to offer. Please feel free to visit any that you find interesting.
Shizuku: (Oh, we get to start visiting clubs tomorrow...?)
Shizuku: (Hehe. I'll be looking forward to that.)
Student: Class is adjourned!
Airi: Shizuku! I know you've been pretty busy lately, but are you thinking about joining a club?
Shizuku: Yes, things have been busy, but I am hoping to join a club and participate as much as I can. What about you, Airi?
Airi: Yeah, my choices are limited because of work, so I'm thinking about joining the tea ceremony club.
Airi: Have you already picked one out, Shizuku?
Shizuku: I still don't know if I'm going to actually join, but I'd like to visit the archery club...
Airi: Archery? That's really cool!
Airi: Being an idol obviously takes priority, but who can blame us for wanting to enjoy high school life? Let's both make the most of our time here!
Shizuku: Hehe. I agree. Let's have as much fun as we can as idols and students!
Shizuku: So this is what it's like to have all this archery gear on...
Shizuku: I wasn't expecting to get a chance to wear it since I'm just here to visit. Hehe. This is so wonderful...
Archery Club Captain: Prospective club members, do you all have your gear on?
Shizuku & the First Years: Yes!
Archery Club Captain: First, allow me to introduce myself! My name is Hayashi, the captain of the archery club! I hope you all enjoy your visit!
Archery Club Captain: Next, we'd like to hear from each of you. Oh, it'd also be nice to hear why you decided to visit.
Archery Club Captain: Starting with...you!
Shizuku: Huh? O-Of course...!
First Years: Whoa...! She's gorgeous! Who is she?!
Second Years: Wait, isn't that...? She's in Cheerful * Days!
Shizuku: U-Umm...
Shizuku: My name is Shizuku Hinomori. I'm in Class 1-D.
Shizuku: I decided to visit the archery club because...a friend of mine used to do archery and said it's a nice way to improve one's posture...
Shizuku: (How much should I reveal...? Should I mention in advance that I'm an idol and may not be able to participate much...and risk making it awkward? Or later after I've actually joined...?)
Shizuku: So...
Shizuku: I-I'd like to make the most of today's visit.
Archery Club Captain: Wonderful! Thank you, Hinomori!
First Years: She seems kinda different compared to when she's on TV...
First Years: Yeah. I was under the impression that she was more mature and articulate.
Shizuku: Oh...
???: Hinomori, right...?
???: I was impressed. I wish you the best of luck.
Shizuku: Huh...? You were impressed?
???: Yes, because your posture is already very good. The fact that you wish to further improve it left an impression on me.
Shizuku: Oh... Thank you...
???: Hehe. There's no need to thank me. I was just saying what I felt.
Shizuku: (Did she notice that I'm feeling a little down? Was she trying to cheer me up...?)
Shizuku: (That's so kind of her. And we only just met...)
Archery Club Captain: Alright, how about... You, next to her!
???: Sure...
Shizuku: (Oh, now it's her turn... I wonder why she chose to visit the archery club.)
Mafuyu: My name is Mafuyu Asahina. I'm in Class 1-A and attended the junior high school here.
Mafuyu: I decided to visit the archery club because...
Mafuyu: The captain handed me a flyer after the entrance ceremony.
Archery Club Captain: What?
Mafuyu: I thought this club would be fun after seeing the way she was smiling as she handed flyers out...
Archery Club Captain: R-Really?! I feel kind of embarrassed now...
Second Years: Haha! But that's what makes you so great, Captain!
Mafuyu: I'm a novice in terms of archery, so I hope you'll understand. And I'm looking forward to learning from all of you today.
Shizuku: Oh...
Shizuku: (Not only is she kind, she's also mature and has this uncanny ability to create an uplifting atmosphere...)
Shizuku: What a wonderful person...
Archery Club Captain: We'll begin with some strength drills! Archery is a sport that requires you to have a solid core!
Archery Club Captain: Let's start with five sets of thirty-second planks! Everyone, ready?
First Years: M-My abs hurt so much...!
Shizuku: (Phew... I somehow managed.)
Shizuku: (I need to be perfect in order to avoid any more harm to my image...!)
Second Years: Oh, Hinomori, you seem to be doing just fine. Are these sorts of exercises a normal part of an idol's routine?
Shizuku: Yes, our dance lessons usually involve these sorts of exercises.
Second Years: That's so interesting! Oh, Asahina's not doing too bad either...
Shizuku: (Oh...)
Second Years: Asahina's really kicking butt! Were you in a sports club during junior high?
Mafuyu: No, I wasn't actually in a club, but I did help out from time to time.
Archery Club Captain: Really?! That makes what you're doing now even more incredible.
Shizuku: (I agree... She can handle this just fine despite not training on a regular basis...)
Archery Club Captain: Next, we'll use these training bows with rubber bands to practice drawing the string. Remember the eight steps that we just showed and try to put them into practice.
First Years: I-It's heavier than I thought... I can't draw it...
First Years: I'm trying too... But it's so hard just to stay in this position.
Shizuku: Hnng...!
Second Years: Oh, Hinomori, you're doing great! Not many people can draw like that on their first attempt!
Shizuku: Th-Thank you very much!
Shizuku: (But it's so difficult to keep it drawn...)
Shizuku: (The others make it look so easy too... I had no idea how physically demanding this was...!)
Shizuku: Eep!!!
Second Years: Oh no! The band...! Are you okay? Did you get hurt?
Shizuku: Y-Yes, I'm okay... I'm so sorry. My hand slipped...
Shizuku: (I was so close... But I failed...)
Archery Club Captain: Way to go, Asahina! And you had a perfect follow-through!
Shizuku: What?
Mafuyu: I did? Wonderful...!
Mafuyu: It was so much trouble in the beginning just drawing it back...
Mafuyu: But I managed to figure it out after seeing you do it yourself. So, thank you very much.
First Years: That was so cool, Asahina! Can you show me how you did that?
Mafuyu: Um... Based on what I was told, you need to use your whole body to...
First Years: Oh, okay! I think I get it now!
Shizuku: (That's astounding... She's already figured out how to do it...)
Shizuku: (And she's teaching those around her...)
Shizuku: She must be the true definition of perfect...
Shizuku: (If only I could do what she can...)
Archery Club Captain: Asahina, if you don't plan on joining any of the other clubs, would you like to join ours? I have a feeling that archery suits you very well!
Mafuyu: Oh... Thank you for the offer... Umm...
Mafuyu: I did have quite a lot of fun today and wish to learn more... So, I think I'll accept.
Archery Club Captain: You will?! Thank you so much!
Shizuku: (She's joining...)
Shizuku: (What should I do...?)
Shizuku: (I thought it'd be fun to give this a try and learn how to shoot...)
Shizuku: (But it ended up being more difficult than I realized. I'm still getting on my feet as an idol, so I may end up becoming a burden if I'm not careful...)
Shizuku: (Things may have turned out differently if only I were perfect like Asahina...)
Mafuyu: Are you not going to join, Hinomori?
Shizuku: Me? U-Um, I...
Mafuyu: I'm still a novice when it comes to archery, but I think it also suits you very well...
Shizuku: I appreciate the compliment... But why do you think that?
Mafuyu: Not only is your posture beautiful, but the stern expression you made as you drew your bow really showed your determination.
Mafuyu: So, I thought it'd be fun if we could do this together.
Shizuku: Asahina...
Archery Club Captain: Asahina! Here's the form for joining! Write your name and class in these spaces.
Archery Club Captain: How about you, Hinomori?
Shizuku: I, um...!
Shizuku: I'd like to join as well.
